message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a computationally efficient method for automatic coronary calcium scoring using ConvNets, which involves image registration and direct regression of calcium score. This suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on medical imaging and cardiovascular disease, indicating that it could also belong to the medical imaging (cs.MED) or neuroscience (cs.NEURON) sub-categories.
